## Tab containing both a code block and an alert

{% tabs %}
{% tab label="Setup" %}
{% alert level="tip" %}
Run this command in a virtual environment to avoid conflicts with system packages.
{% /alert %}

```bash
pip install datadog && pip install datadog-api-client
```

Pellentesque habitant morbi tristique senectus et netus et malesuada fames ac turpis egestas.
{% /tab %}
{% tab label="Configuration" %}
{% alert level="warning" %}
Store your API key in an environment variable, not in source code.
{% /alert %}

```bash
export DD_API_KEY="YOUR_API_KEY"
export DD_APP_KEY="YOUR_APP_KEY"
```

Curabitur pretium tincidunt lacus. Nulla gravida orci a odio. Nullam varius, turpis et commodo pharetra.
{% /tab %}
{% tab label="Verification" %}
{% alert level="info" %}
A successful response returns status code 200 with a JSON body.
{% /alert %}

```python
from datadog_api_client import ApiClient, Configuration

config = Configuration()
with ApiClient(config) as api_client:
    print("Connected successfully")
```
{% /tab %}
{% /tabs %}

